{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Ewu5AvZquLg5EXCcsXbzwS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the StatefulSet is patched. This will trigger a rolling update. But the ConfigMap update (for probe.sh) won't automatically trigger a pod restart - I need to restart the pods manually to pick up the new ConfigMap.\n\nWait, actually the StatefulSet patch will trigger a rolling update because the pod template has changed. But the ConfigMap change won't trigger a restart automatically since it's a ConfigMap (not part of the pod spec hash).\n\nHmm, but I patched the StatefulSet with new probe settings which are different from the current ones - this should trigger a rolling update. The pods will restart one by one. \n\nActually, I'm realizing there's a complication with how probe.sh is mounted. Since it's mounted via `subPath` from the ConfigMap, updates to the ConfigMap won't be automatically propagated to the running pods - the kubelet doesn't refresh files mounted with `subPath` the way it does for full volume mounts. So even though the pods will restart from the StatefulSet update, I need to make sure the new probe.sh actually gets picked up when they come back up.\n\nBut there's another issue I'm hitting: when the pods restart, the health-user might not exist yet, and the probe checks if that user can authenticate. If the probe fails because of auth issues, the pod won't become Ready, which creates a catch-22 where I need the pods running to initialize the replica set, but the pods won't become Ready until the replica set is initialized.\n\nThe localhost exception in MongoDB might help here—if no users exist in the admin database, connections from localhost don't require credentials. But once users are created, that exception is disabled. I need to check the current state after the rolling update starts and see if I can initialize the replica set before the probes start failing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":355,"cache_read_input_tokens":42867,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":355},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5c4fbd6d-a34b-4d9a-ad8b-c0beb9d2fd08","uuid":"c89f226e-b2ed-4adc-8cd7-bf3174a4416d","request_id":"req_011CcRGxHiAVR8bgKkhmoGX8"}
